Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.35,0:00:14.27,JoJo-internal/narrator,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,"Which creature walks on \Nfour legs in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.27,0:00:17.54,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,two legs in the afternoon,\Nand three legs in the evening?"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.98,0:00:22.20,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,The guardian of the pyramids,\Nthe Sphinx, asked travelers this riddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.74,0:00:24.61,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,The answer is "Humans."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.00,0:00:29.09,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,Legend says that those who could\Nnot answer were eaten by the Sphinx.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.05,0:00:32.39,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty thousand kilometers from Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.75,0:00:36.25,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,Jotaro and the others have finally reached Cairo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.56,0:00:39.08,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Cairo is immense.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.08,0:00:40.72,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than searching aimlessly,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.72,0:00:44.13,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,we should work our way from \Nthe outskirts inward to the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.95,0:00:51.57,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,We're finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.68,0:01:00.30,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,Jotaro and the others have arrived in Cairo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.26,0:01:04.44,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,But before the pyramid named DIO,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.44,0:01:07.95,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,a few more Sphinxes stood in their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.70,0:01:24.30,JoJo-main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, foreigners. What would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.30,0:01:26.27,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.07,0:01:31.13,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,We're looking for the building in this picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.13,0:01:32.78,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.73,0:01:36.36,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,Joseph and the others were exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.85,0:01:38.87,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since their arrival,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.87,0:01:41.74,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,they had searched constantly \Nfor the building in the picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.61,0:01:46.04,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,These are spirit pictures that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.04,0:01:48.29,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,Joseph managed to take of DIO's mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.91,0:01:50.52,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,DIO had moved to a new hideout,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.52,0:01:53.62,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,and the Speedwagon Foundation \Nhad lost track of his whereabouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.45,0:01:56.23,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,Where is DIO?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.83,0:01:59.36,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,If they are unable to find \Nhim in the next few days,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.36,0:02:01.29,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,Holly's life will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.63,0:02:08.64,JoJo-main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sirs, this is a café. Please order something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.38,0:02:11.79,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Four iced teas.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.62,0:02:26.04,JoJo-main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, I don't recognize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.62,0:02:38.08,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Cairo has a population of six million.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.08,0:02:40.49,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,There must be two to three million buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.49,0:02:42.18,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Will we be able to find him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.44,0:02:43.78,JoJo-internal/narrator,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,There has to be someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.78,0:02:45.75,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone has to know where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.86,0:02:49.83,JoJo-main,manb,0000,0000,0000,,This building, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.83,0:02:51.69,JoJo-main,mabc,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell from just a picture...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.69,0:02:54.15,JoJo-main,man,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, it doesn't look familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.86,0:02:57.22,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Sorry to bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.22,0:02:58.15,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.15,0:03:00.32,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Let's continue our investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.59,0:03:08.95,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I know that building.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.95,0:03:09.96,JoJo-main,all,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.92,0:03:16.09,JoJo-main,dary,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt about it. It's {\i1}that{\i0} building.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.15,0:03:24.04,JoJo-Spread,sfx,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,963)}Spread
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.93,0:04:57.19,JoJo-MainTitle,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(208,2515)}JoJo's {\c&H2E0FB2&}Bizarre Adventure
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.35,0:04:57.19,JoJo-MainTitle2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(208,2515)}Stardust Crusaders
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.59,0:05:05.52,JoJo-EpTitle,title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(672,466)}Episode 34  D'Arby the Gambler, Part 1
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.54,0:05:05.78,JoJo-top,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,W-Was it you who just said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.84,0:05:11.73,JoJo-Location,derp,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(459,459)\b0\fs18}This story is fiction. The characters, groups, places, laws, and names \Nused in this program have no connection to any existing in real life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.08,0:05:08.28,JoJo-top,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I just heard someone say \Nthey know this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.53,0:05:10.24,JoJo-top,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.04,0:05:16.43,JoJo-top,,0000,0000,0000,,I did indeed say that I know where\Nthe mansion in that picture is located.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.84,0:05:18.83,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,What? Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.83,0:05:20.46,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,That's great to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.46,0:05:23.70,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! We're pretty lucky to have \Nfound someone who knows
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.70,0:05:25.26,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,where it is just from this picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.43,0:05:28.40,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Where? Please tell us! Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.46,0:05:39.06,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Are you asking me to give \Nyou the answer for free?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.06,0:05:42.67,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You've got a point. Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.67,0:05:44.32,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pay you ten pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.32,0:05:46.26,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,So, where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.00,0:05:54.17,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I love gambling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.17,0:05:56.69,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a sucker for cheap thrills.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.69,0:05:58.71,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't get enough of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:06:03.17,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you could say that \NI make my living gambling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.93,0:06:06.80,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Do you like gambling?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.80,0:06:10.03,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure what you're getting at.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.58,0:06:14.64,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't like gambling, just say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.64,0:06:18.27,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you exactly what you mean by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.61,0:06:23.36,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Well... Would you make a\Nsilly little wager with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.89,0:06:28.70,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,If you win, I'll tell you \Nwhere that place is for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.70,0:06:31.44,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Wager? I'm pretty confident \Nwhen it comes to wagers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.44,0:06:34.82,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,but we don't have time \Nto play poker right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.82,0:06:37.41,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you another twenty pounds, \Nso please just tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.70,0:06:41.02,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,The thing about gambling is, \Nyou can do it with anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.02,0:06:42.96,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,It won't take any time at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.82,0:06:45.17,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,For example,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.17,0:06:48.76,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,look over there. See that cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.15,0:07:00.62,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Now, why don't we bet on which\Nsmoked fish that cat will eat first?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.62,0:07:03.15,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Right or left?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.41,0:07:06.94,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,How about it? It's silly, but thrilling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.79,0:07:10.22,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You're really starting to annoy me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.22,0:07:14.46,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,Just take the thirty pounds, \Nand hurry up and tell us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.46,0:07:18.51,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Polnareff, that's not the way to \Nask someone for information.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.04,0:07:21.93,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, fine! Then I'll make a bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.93,0:07:23.79,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I pick the one on the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.79,0:07:26.60,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Good! Now it's getting fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.60,0:07:29.05,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I shall wager on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.48,0:07:31.01,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.24,0:07:35.44,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Jotaro. Isn't he rather suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.44,0:07:38.45,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... He might be an enemy Stand user.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.23,0:07:41.97,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,But he might just be a compulsive gambler.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.33,0:07:47.59,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,If he does anything even remotely strange,\Nplow through him with Star Platinum.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.59,0:07:48.63,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.56,0:07:53.83,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, if I lose,\Nwhat am I supposed to pay you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.83,0:07:55.25,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,Like, a hundred pounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.25,0:07:57.03,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need money.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.69,0:08:01.51,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,How about your soul? I'll take your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.96,0:08:04.23,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.23,0:08:07.38,JoJo-internal/narrator,jean,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of joke is that? Cocky bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.38,0:08:10.87,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to hurry up and\Nget the hell away from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.87,0:08:12.05,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Your answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.05,0:08:15.35,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, okay, sure. That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.56,0:08:21.29,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? The cat has taken \Nnotice of the smoked fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.16,0:08:23.14,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,The right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.57,0:08:26.69,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,The kitty's going to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.32,0:08:30.72,JoJo-internal/narrator,jean,0000,0000,0000,,If I were a cat, I'd pick the bigger one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.72,0:08:33.07,JoJo-internal/narrator,jean,0000,0000,0000,,The one on the right looks bigger!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.25,0:08:46.90,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,You saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.90,0:08:50.49,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,It first took the left, \Nthen the right, and then ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.49,0:08:52.34,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I win.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.34,0:08:55.99,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you lost, Polnareff. \NWhat are you going to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.99,0:09:00.07,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting sick of asking \Naround about that building.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.19,0:09:05.45,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then. As per our agreement, \Nlet's have you pay up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.45,0:09:08.01,JoJo-main,jean,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Pay? Pay what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.54,0:09:10.36,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.26,0:09:14.15,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,That is indeed what you just wagered.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.96,0:09:16.39,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Your soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.39,0:09:19.24,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I am a Stand user that steals souls!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.57,0:09:24.74,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Gambling makes it easier for the \Nhuman soul to leave its vessel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.74,0:09:28.59,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,It is my Stand's power to\Nsteal it at that moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.78,0:09:36.47,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,What?! What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.90,0:09:36.46,JoJo-Blam,sfx,0000,0000,0000,,Grab
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.47,0:09:37.47,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Polnareff!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.27,0:09:41.71,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it! Don't kill me. It's too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.10,0:09:47.31,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,If I die, Polnareff's soul, which is \Nin my Stand's grasp, will also die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.31,0:09:48.40,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Polnareff!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.13,0:09:50.39,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.60,0:09:53.61,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,H-He has no pulse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.88,0:09:57.32,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead! Polnareff is dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.11,0:10:01.49,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Polnareff!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.34,0:10:21.63,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,This is Polnareff's soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.63,0:10:23.86,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,This means I've already gotten rid of one
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.86,0:10:25.81,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,of the people trying to get in Lord DIO's way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.81,0:10:27.88,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Even if he was just a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.71,0:10:31.95,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little overdue,\Nbut allow me to introduce myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.31,0:10:34.32,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,My name is D'Arby.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.56,0:10:40.26,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,D-A-R-B-Y. There's an apostrophe after the D.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.41,0:10:44.60,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,The Stand that steals souls \Nfrom those who lost a bet...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.03,0:10:46.96,JoJo-internal/narrator,nar,0000,0000,0000,,The one that suggests Osiris.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.79,0:10:53.88,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, this is my cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.88,0:10:56.38,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.78,0:11:01.30,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Don't screw with us! A bet? It was just a scam!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.30,0:11:02.55,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,A scam?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.55,0:11:05.44,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. If you've been scammed,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.44,0:11:07.81,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the one who failed to see through it is the loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.69,0:11:12.19,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I believe gambling is just like relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.19,0:11:14.76,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,It's all about fooling the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.29,0:11:17.98,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,The one who cries loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.22,0:11:22.46,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to kill me with your bare hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.03,0:11:25.31,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.31,0:11:29.01,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want this soul to die, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.01,0:11:30.38,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Listen here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.38,0:11:33.40,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,You will not walk away from this in one piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.04,0:11:38.68,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember what you \Nwere doing on the night of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.68,0:11:41.88,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,September 22nd, 1984 at 11:15 PM?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.88,0:11:43.36,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.37,0:11:47.34,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.16,0:11:50.93,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Around that time in California,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.93,0:11:54.64,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I was gambling with an American \Nman named Stephen Moor,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.64,0:11:57.57,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and he said the same thing you just did.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.88,0:12:04.41,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,This is him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.68,0:12:10.08,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,The one below is Moor's father, \Nand his wife is right next to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.81,0:12:15.53,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to get Polnareff's soul back,\Nyou have no choice but to continue
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.97,0:12:18.18,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,gambling with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.49,0:12:22.01,JoJo-internal/narrator,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This man is a demon...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.01,0:12:24.77,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,He's planning to take us, one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.45,0:12:28.31,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.31,0:12:30.64,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're scared, you can go home...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.64,0:12:33.33,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,And leave Polnareff behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.65,0:12:39.02,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Well, have a drink and think \Nabout it long and hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.61,0:12:40.90,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,How about some chocolate?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.53,0:13:02.63,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mr. Joestar, what are you trying to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.50,0:13:08.32,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Have you heard of surface tension, Barbie?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.32,0:13:11.67,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,It's D'Arby. My name is D'Arby.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.35,0:13:17.21,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,It's the force that's keeping that drink \Nfrom breaking the surface, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.77,0:13:19.86,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,What do you plan to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.86,0:13:21.73,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,The rules are simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.73,0:13:25.07,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take turns putting coins in this glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.69,0:13:27.87,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,The one who makes it overflow loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.11,0:13:29.10,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.10,0:13:31.48,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't mean... Mr. Joestar!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.29,0:13:36.40,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wager my soul on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.32,0:13:42.96,JoJo-Eyecatch3,signtop,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(541,1)}Osiris
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.98,0:13:42.96,JoJo-Eyecatch2,signbot,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(966,1)}D'Arby Elder
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.45,0:13:46.26,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wager my soul on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.26,0:13:47.38,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.38,0:13:49.09,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.09,0:13:52.92,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible! P-Please don't! He's a con artist!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.92,0:13:54.33,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let him cheat!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.33,0:13:56.90,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who chose the method of this wager!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.90,0:13:59.10,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Jotaro, make sure he doesn't cheat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.47,0:14:04.18,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! That's fine. I shall take this bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.74,0:14:06.32,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,But first...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.32,0:14:09.70,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mind if I inspect the glass and coins?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.70,0:14:11.45,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, you have that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.66,0:14:14.53,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,You also have the right to \Nmake sure I'm not cheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.15,0:14:25.15,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,First, will you guarantee that if you lose,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.15,0:14:28.18,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,you will return Polnareff's \Nsoul, no matter what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.52,0:14:34.26,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I am a gambler. I do have my pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.66,0:14:38.89,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,If I lose, I always pay up.\NI won't lose, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.40,0:14:44.02,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. You can go first. Put in a coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.02,0:14:45.47,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Joestar!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.47,0:14:47.26,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Just leave this to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.35,0:14:51.50,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I'm an expert at this trick with a glass and coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.95,0:14:55.02,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not easy to beat when \Nsurface tension is involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.49,0:14:58.76,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,It should fit about eight or nine more coins...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.18,0:15:02.96,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I can remain calm \Nand my fingers don't shake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.32,0:15:06.87,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,May I put in more than one coin at a time?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.87,0:15:09.17,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,If you can do it all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.17,0:15:10.13,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.25,0:15:12.97,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,F-Five?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.97,0:15:14.98,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I think I saw a little wave there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.98,0:15:15.72,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.26,0:15:20.50,JoJo-main,daarby,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.14,0:15:47.84,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,It's your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.14,0:15:52.00,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Your guts are quite impressive,\Nto put in five at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.43,0:15:54.35,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go with one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.35,0:15:55.85,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,That was too close.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.46,0:16:02.81,JoJo-internal/narrator,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,The old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.19,0:16:05.48,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,He has cotton between his finger and the coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.22,0:16:08.56,JoJo-internal/narrator,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Liquid is dripping from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.56,0:16:10.90,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,He's squeezing it out and adding to the alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.17,0:16:13.66,JoJo-internal/narrator,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,And you wanted me to watch for cheating?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.66,0:16:15.06,JoJo-internal/narrator,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,You scoundrel...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.52,0:16:17.16,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.30,0:16:28.40,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,No more will fit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.40,0:16:31.92,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,Even one more and the\Ndrink will spill over! I've won!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.22,0:16:37.05,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a scam if you're not caught!\NThat's what he said himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.52,0:16:41.38,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad for my heart.\NI thought it was going to spill...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.83,0:16:44.60,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's your turn, Obie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.46,0:16:49.30,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,It's D'Arby. Don't mistake that again!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.30,0:16:51.44,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is D'Arby!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.67,0:16:53.74,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,It's not Obie or Barbie!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.89,0:16:56.20,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.38,0:17:00.85,JoJo-internal/narrator,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,He's screwing up his name on \Npurpose to make him agitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.85,0:17:02.33,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,That old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.33,0:17:04.34,JoJo-internal/narrator,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,He's a gambler at heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.89,0:17:07.05,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Let's continue our wager.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.05,0:17:11.42,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your turn to put in a coin, D'Arby.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.40,0:17:23.31,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,There's a shadow, so this angle is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.63,0:17:26.39,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I'll put it in from the right side of the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.39,0:17:28.81,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,You may put it in from wherever you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.19,0:17:33.83,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Though because of my cheat, \Nit's already at its limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.83,0:17:36.50,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't put any more in, \Nno matter what he tries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.50,0:17:39.42,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,It'll overflow if he even touches the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.71,0:17:51.51,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,You're thinking that this glass's \Nsurface tension is at it's limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.51,0:17:53.87,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,That it's impossible, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.32,0:17:57.84,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not true...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.82,0:18:08.18,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I-Impossible! It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.18,0:18:10.58,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way it wouldn't overflow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.95,0:18:14.33,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean,\Nthere's no way it wouldn't overflow?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.71,0:18:16.87,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, it went in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.01,0:18:21.21,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,He made no suspicious moves \Nthat could've been cheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.21,0:18:23.08,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,I was watching with Star Platinum.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:26.45,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,He put the coin in fairly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.96,0:18:28.08,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,There's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.56,0:18:30.94,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,B-But I made sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.32,0:18:35.87,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I made sure that it would \Noverflow if one more was added!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.87,0:18:39.12,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Why? There's no way one \Nmore could have gone in!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.12,0:18:40.80,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,So how?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.80,0:18:43.64,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead, Mr. Joestar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.64,0:18:45.37,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.37,0:18:48.27,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Or are you trying to wait until it evaporates?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.46,0:19:01.75,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I-I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.20,0:19:31.07,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Joestar!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.26,0:19:42.82,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Joestar acknowledged in his mind\Nthat he'd already lost the bet!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.82,0:19:45.45,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,That's why his soul emerged.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.45,0:19:48.59,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I, D'Arby, have won this bet!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.57,0:19:53.24,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Polnareff, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.24,0:19:57.72,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Holly, I might not be\Nable to save you, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.81,0:20:01.88,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Joestar!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.88,0:20:02.83,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.16,0:20:12.41,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,That's two!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.41,0:20:14.55,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then. Let us continue gambling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.20,0:20:17.33,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you two don't abandon
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.33,0:20:21.04,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,these two and run away with your \Ntails between your legs, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.68,0:20:24.16,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.73,0:20:27.42,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,You don't learn, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.42,0:20:31.71,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,If you kill me, these two souls will die, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.71,0:20:32.78,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.78,0:20:34.25,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Avdol, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.25,0:20:37.09,JoJo-main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! If you're going to make trouble, \NI'll have to ask you to leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.09,0:20:39.13,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Shut it. Stay out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.13,0:20:40.24,JoJo-main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.39,0:20:59.07,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,You realized it too late, Jotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.77,0:21:01.65,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something wrong with the glass?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.97,0:21:04.71,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,This is how one more coin went in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.42,0:21:09.31,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,There was a tiny bit of chocolate \Non the bottom of the glass's outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.98,0:21:11.85,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Before they started the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.85,0:21:15.70,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,he asked to inspect the glass and coins,\Nand that's when he stuck it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.53,0:21:18.52,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I believe you were aware that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.52,0:21:21.79,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,if it's not discovered in time,\Nyou can't call it cheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.79,0:21:23.46,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.46,0:21:26.64,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,How is a bit of chocolate \Nthe reason the coin fit?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.65,0:21:29.30,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,It's melted now,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.30,0:21:32.45,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,but until a moment ago, it was \Nsolid at the bottom of the glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.29,0:21:35.54,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,He used just enough so we wouldn't notice,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.45,0:21:38.34,Jojo-Signs1,left,0000,0000,0000,,This side will spill
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.45,0:21:38.35,Jojo-Signs2,right,0000,0000,0000,,Glass is tilted
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.54,0:21:37.94,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,but the glass was propped up so it would tilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.94,0:21:42.03,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Once it melted, the surface became level.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.35,0:21:42.55,Jojo-Signs1,left,0000,0000,0000,,Surface tension becomes equal
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.35,0:21:42.55,Jojo-Signs3,right,0000,0000,0000,,It melts
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.71,0:21:44.81,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Even though the surface tension was at its limit,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.81,0:21:48.03,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,he made it so at least one more coin would fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.03,0:21:50.01,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.01,0:21:51.60,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.60,0:21:55.54,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Could chocolate actually melt\Nwith such convenient timing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.08,0:21:58.30,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,He melted it using the sun's heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.30,0:21:59.62,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.41,0:22:02.84,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,He went to the right side of the table
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.84,0:22:06.84,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,so the sun's rays would directly hit \Nthe glass and melt the chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.53,0:22:17.65,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.65,0:22:21.23,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,D'Arby, get your trump card ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.48,0:22:23.19,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll finish this with poker.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.78,0:22:26.69,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,J-Jotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.30,0:22:55.26,JoJo-Rumble,sfx,0000,0000,0000,,Rumble
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.62,0:22:29.09,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,How interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.09,0:22:33.04,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Poker is one of the games I'm best at!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.04,0:22:37.65,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,Poker? This man just beat Mr. Joestar!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.65,0:22:39.00,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's too dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.00,0:22:40.17,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.17,0:22:42.23,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not violent,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.23,0:22:45.78,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,but he's still more dangerous than \Nany other Stand user we've met so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.06,0:22:47.85,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.34,0:22:55.76,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,I can't afford not to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.01,0:23:37.01,JoJo-Preview,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Next Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.28,0:23:37.56,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Draw three.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.56,0:23:39.10,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,I'll draw two.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.10,0:23:41.40,JoJo-main,avdol,0000,0000,0000,,He's not doing anything suspicious, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.40,0:23:43.98,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Cheating is all about finding a mental blind spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.98,0:23:45.54,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one joker.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.54,0:23:47.11,JoJo-main,darby,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then, Jotaro...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.11,0:23:50.03,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. I'll wager my soul.
